er to duplicate something if it reduces code complexity, like implementing abstract methods that throw exceptions. I need to figure out if I should include @BeforeAll for setting the system property statically, while also being cautious about how static initializers interact with nested classes.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering test property management**\\n\\nI’m thinking it’s global only in this test process, and the existing tests may not be dependent on any properties, so maybe I shouldn't restore them. But leaving things unclean isn't great. Setting the property statically and leaving it could help for the test environment where the API has no implementation. I wonder if checking the style would indicate that system properties should be restored, but if the class is already loaded, then maybe it’s unnecessary. What if there are parallel tests? I need to be cautious about fallback failures if other tests instantiate ExpressionFactory afterward.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_IaBgLhoEhNqhHexxJ6C5xaJj|fc_01af05cf99107ebd016a01d9fe24c88195b075385ed71cab48", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/jakarta.platform/jakarta.jakartaee-api/10.0.0/src/test/java/jakarta_platform/jakarta_jakartaee_api/ELProcessorTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage jakarta_platform.jakarta_jakartaee_api;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\nimport jakarta.el.ELContext;\nimport jakarta.el.ELProcessor;\nimport jakarta.el.ExpressionFactory;\nimport jakarta.el.MethodExpression;\nimport jakarta.el.ValueExpression;\n\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\npublic class ELProcessorTest {\n    private static final String EXPRESSION_FACTORY_PROPERTY = \"jakarta.el.ExpressionFactory\";\n\n    static {\n        System.setProperty(EXPRESSION_FACTORY_PROPERTY, TestExpressionFactory.class.getName());\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void defineFunctionWithMethodNameScansDeclaredMethods() throws Exception {\n        ELProcessor processor = new ELProcessor();\n\n        processor.defineFunction(\"text\", \"echo\", Functions.class.getName(), \"echo\");\n\n        assertThat(processor.getELManager().getELContext().getFunctionMapper().resolveFunction(\"text\", \"echo\"))\n                .isNotNull()\n                .extracting(method -> method.getName())\n                .isEqualTo(\"echo\");\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void defineFunctionWithSignatureResolvesArrayParameterTypes() throws Exception {\n        ELProcessor processor = new ELProcessor();\n\n        processor.defineFunction(\n                \"text\",\n                \"combine\",\n                Functions.class.getName(),\n                \"java.lang.String combine(java.lang.String,java.lang.String[],java.lang.String[][])\");\n\n        assertThat(processor.getELManager().getELContext().getFunctionMapper().resolveFunction(\"text\", \"combine\"))\n                .isNotNull()\n                .extracting(method -> method.getName())\n                .isEqualTo(\"combine\");\n    }\n\n    public static class Functions {\n        public static String echo(String value) {\n            return value;\n        }\n\n        public static String combine(String prefix, String[] values, String[][] groupedValues) {\n            return prefix + values.length + groupedValues.length;\n        }\n    }\n\n    public static class TestExpressionFactory extends ExpressionFactory {\n        @Override\n        public ValueExpression createValueExpression(ELContext context, String expression, Class<?> expectedType) {\n            throw new UnsupportedOperationException(\"Expression parsing is not needed by these tests\");\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public ValueExpression createValueExpression(Object instance, Class<?> expectedType) {\n            throw new UnsupportedOperationException(\"Expression parsing is not needed by these tests\");\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public MethodExpression createMethodExpression(\n                ELContext context,\n                String expression,\n                Class<?> expectedReturnType,\n                Class<?>[] expectedParamTypes) {\n            throw new UnsupportedOperationException(\"Expression parsing is not needed by these tests\");\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public <T> T coerceToType(Object obj, Class<T> targetType) {\n            throw new UnsupportedOperationException(\"Type coercion is not needed by these tests\");\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 476, "output": 2853, "cacheRead": 24576, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 27905, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778506206249, "responseId": "resp_01af05cf99107ebd016a01d9dec3348195838411479c32f142"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_IaBgLhoEhNqhHexxJ6C5xaJj|fc_01af05cf99107ebd016a01d9fe24c88195b075385ed71cab48", "toolName": "write", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Successfully wrote 3261 bytes to tests/src/jakarta.platform/jakarta.jakartaee-api/10.0.0/src/test/java/jakarta_platform/jakarta_jakartaee_api/ELProcessorTest.java"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1778506242480}]}
